  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse the <strong>brown rice</strong>, add it to a large pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p>\r\n<p>Quarter the <strong>chestnut mushrooms&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Slice the<strong> pak&nbsp;choi&nbsp;</strong>into wedges</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over the<strong>&nbsp;highest heat</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once very hot, add a splash of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and the<strong> beef strips</strong> and cook for 1-2 min on each side or until they're browned</p>\r\n<p>Tip: don't overcook the beef or it will go chewy! If your pan is small, cook it in batches</p>\r\n<p>Transfer the <strong>cooked beef strips</strong> to a large plate and set them aside to rest</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong>&nbsp;quartered mushrooms</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to brown</p>\r\n<p>Once browned, transfer the <strong>mushrooms</strong> to the plate with the beef strips and return the pan to a low heat</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped ginger</strong> to the pan and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong> balsamic vinegar</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>honey</strong>,<strong>&nbsp;miso paste</strong>&nbsp;and a splash of <strong>water</strong> and cook for 4-5 min &ndash; this is your <strong>ginger sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1333.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>brown rice</strong> is cooked, add the <strong>pak choi halves&nbsp;</strong>to the pot with the<strong> rice</strong>&nbsp;and cook, covered, for a further 3 min or until tender</p>\r\n<p>Once done,&nbsp;remove the<strong> pak choi</strong>&nbsp;and set it aside</p>\r\n<p>Drain the<strong>&nbsp;brown rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
